cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.SY

The paper proposes a novel batch optimization algorithm for black-box optimization, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. The paper also derives regret bounds for both noise-free and perturbation settings, which are common in optimization theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves optimization theory, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a criterion for generating initialization point sets, which involves system identification and control theory, suggesting cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
